TY  - JOUR
AU  - Chen, Hong
AU  - Frank, Murray Z
T1  - The Effect of Taxation on Corporate Financing and Investment
PY  - 2022
Y1  - 2022/02/01
DO  - 10.1093/rcfs/cfab005
JO  - The Review of Corporate Finance Studies
JA  - Review of Corporate Finance Studies
VL  - 11
IS  - 1
SP  - 47
EP  - 87
SN  - 2046-9128
AB  - Extensive empirical research concerning the impact of taxes on corporate decisions has had trouble identifying seemingly obvious effects. Perhaps the problem is that the seemingly obvious tax predictions are not quite right. We provide an equilibrium model with both corporate and personal taxes. In the steady-state equilibrium, the corporate tax rate affects the level of production despite interest deductibility at the firm level, but not household-level taxes on interest earnings or dividends. We prove several other tax irrelevance results and document a Laffer curve in the corporate tax rate. (JEL G31, G32, G35)
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rcfs/cfab005
ER  - 



