TY  - JOUR
AU  - Venugopal, Buvaneshwaran
AU  - Yerramilli, Vijay
T1  - Seed-Stage Success and Growth of Angel Co-investment Networks*
PY  - 2022
Y1  - 2022/02/01
DO  - 10.1093/rcfs/cfab016
JO  - The Review of Corporate Finance Studies
JA  - Review of Corporate Finance Studies
VL  - 11
IS  - 1
SP  - 169
EP  - 210
SN  - 2046-9128
AB  - Using hand-collected data, we show that coinvestment is widespread in the angel investment market, even among seed-stage startups. Individual angels with demonstrated seed-stage success experience an increase in the quantity, quality, and geographic and industry spread of their coinvestment connections relative to unsuccessful peers and are rewarded with more deal flow. These results are stronger for less-established angels and for angels whose successes are more indicative of their ability. Success also begets more success: the portfolio companies of successful angels are more likely to receive follow-on financing, especially from VC firms. Our results highlight how angels grow their coinvestment networks. (JEL G24, L14, L26, M13).
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rcfs/cfab016
ER  - 



